This paper discusses the assessment of cyber security in industrial control systems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of metrics and approaches such as resilience, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in cyber security assessments. Finally, the paper discusses the specific context of industrial control systems (cs.CY).
